<c01 id="aspace_3ed6f63ceb90b176af710bae8743f517" level="file"><did><unittitle>Three repreints of published articles:</unittitle><container id="aspace_9a9495dc9416d6feb5167fea9fdc4be8" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182879]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_2ed09db47906b561b1309fd9b4a471ad" parent="aspace_9a9495dc9416d6feb5167fea9fdc4be8" type="folder">40</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_b0cdb8413d7c7a4c3a8506181b3ce527"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>1. "A Link in the Chain of Events Leading to American Independence," from the <title>William and Mary Quarterly</title>, <date>Jan. 1946</date> </p><p> 2. "The American Doctrine of Containment." <date>1980</date> (2 copies)</p><p> 3. The Origins of the Union and of the States. Separate from the Proceedings of the Massachusettes Historical Society. Vol. 72, (<date>1957-1960</date>)</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_4774b37bb5d1ef6ebc48e6abaa0d5dbd" level="file"><did><unittitle>Twenty-six letters from Curtis Nettels to Van Wyck Brooks, the American author, critic, and translator</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce" normal="1952/1954" type="inclusive">1952-1954</unitdate><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce" normal="1958/1963" type="inclusive">1958-1963</unitdate><container id="aspace_010dc8e5691bb5828b17d40c90ce645f" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182879]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_c561c01ccf76343da9ae81f1afa476b5" parent="aspace_010dc8e5691bb5828b17d40c90ce645f" type="folder">41</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_f553e296c5fc06ec844358196f5fb445"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>The letters deal mainly with American writers and American literature, some political issues and also discussion of Mr. Brook's books. Some examples of his well known books are: <title>The Wine of the Puritans</title>, <date>1909</date>; <title>America's Coming of Age</title>, <date>1915</date>; <title>The Ordeal of Mark Twain</title>, <date>1920</date>; <title>The Pilgrimage of Henry James</title>, <date>1925</date>; <title>The Life of Emerson</title>, <date>1932</date>; <title>The Flowering of New England</title>, <date>1936</date>; <title>New England: Indian Summer</title>, <date>1940</date>; <title>The World of Washington Irving</title>, <date>1944</date>; <title>The Confident Years</title>, <date>1952</date>; <title>The Writer in America</title>, <date>1953</date>; <title>Helen Keller, Sketch for a Portrait</title>, <date>1956</date>; <title>Days of the Phoenix</title>, 1957</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_fc8ec6aa31972b250d8cc115fcb6a994" level="file"><did><unittitle>Letters</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce" normal="1952/1952">1952</unitdate><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce" normal="1959/1959">1959</unitdate><container id="aspace_d2eb7e40a17c4bbb8e29767b94fb953d" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182879]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_36c9217393f9c468c6b3227b01ad6f7b" parent="aspace_d2eb7e40a17c4bbb8e29767b94fb953d" type="folder">42</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_4cdd80f997a2a46e47e48fedc842f775"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>This folder contains seven photocopies of letters from Van Wyck Brooks to Mr. Nettels. Also, one photocopy of a newspaper clipping written by Curtis Nettels re Van Wyck Brooks</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_c3ffd0e4d76839d70c8edcbef3b44398" level="file"><did><unittitle>One seventy-two page typescript manuscript: "Boyhood Days in a Prarie Town, Memories of Life in Topeka, Kansas, <date>1905-1917</date>," by Curtis Nettels (2 copies)</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce" normal="1905/1917" type="inclusive">1905-1917</unitdate><container id="aspace_377eacd101f3416fd62fec9849a2d5e9" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182879]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_d0db6d5ed81ec58bcc068550723f407c" parent="aspace_377eacd101f3